parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Bosch III ABS system can cause complete brake failure, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates on the dashboard
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal hesitates or skips
the brakes lock up or fail to engage
the vehicle experiences a loss of braking power
the anti-lock message appears on the information center.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high-pressure hose can cause the brake system to pump all brake fluid overboard, leading to complete brake failure and accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause a sudden explosion, resulting in a fire that can spread to other components, such as the wiring harness and catalytic converter, and potentially cause a vehicle fire, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden loud boom or explosion
transmission housing unit breaking into chunks of metal
transmission fluid spraying onto the catalytic converter
fire igniting
burning of wiring harness and right side of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission filter can cause transmission problems, leading to reduced vehicle performance, and potentially cause damage to other transmission components.
symptoms: None reported
but may include symptoms such as transmission slipping
hesitation
or failure to engage gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the right axle seal can cause transmission fluid leaks, leading to reduced vehicle performance, and potentially cause damage to other transmission components.
symptoms: None reported
but may include symptoms such as transmission fluid leaks
vibration
or noise while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pan gasket or oil filter can cause engine oil leaks, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potentially causing a fire or engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the oil pan or oil filter area
oil drips or puddles under the engine
engine oil level drops
engine noise or knocking sounds
engine overheating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EGR (Exhaust Gas Recirculation) valve can cause the engine to run rough, misfire, or stall, leading to decreased engine performance, reduced fuel efficiency, and potentially causing a breakdown or accident.
symptoms: Engine runs rough or misfires
engine stalls or hesitates
decreased engine performance
reduced fuel efficiency
check engine light illuminates.
